00:06:49.967 --> 00:06:54.877
United States, spending by some
estimates hundreds of millions of

00:06:54.877 --> 00:06:59.457
dollars a month on advertising,
trying to hook new users on the app.

00:07:00.607 --> 00:07:05.747
Companies like Facebook and Snapchat were
all too happy to accept TikTok’s money.

00:07:06.197 --> 00:07:10.827
They were getting paid handsomely,
and besides, it didn’t seem like a

00:07:10.827 --> 00:07:15.772
threat - a Chinese app had never had
any real success in the United States.

00:07:16.073 --> 00:07:21.237
American culture is unique, it’s not
something a foreign app can easily

00:07:21.317 --> 00:07:26.677
crack, especially an app from a culture
as different to the US’s as China’s.

00:07:27.947 --> 00:07:31.767
But there was something that these
American technology companies

00:07:32.007 --> 00:07:36.772
hadn’t understood properly, or at
least hadn’t properly appreciated.

00:07:38.042 --> 00:07:39.962
Tiktok was different.

00:07:40.377 --> 00:07:45.199
It didn’t rely on cultural relevance
or understanding, it worked

00:07:45.339 --> 00:07:47.319
in a completely different way.

00:07:48.529 --> 00:07:54.019
And this brings us back to what I hinted
at earlier, in terms of the design of

00:07:54.029 --> 00:07:56.949
the app, how TikTok works on the surface.

00:07:58.449 --> 00:08:03.379
When you think of the other social media
apps you might use, think Instagram,

00:08:03.569 --> 00:08:09.989
Facebook, Snapchat, or Twitter, they
typically work on a “social graph” basis.

00:08:11.402 --> 00:08:14.962
Going back to the early days of
Facebook, you would be friends with

00:08:14.962 --> 00:08:19.462
people, Facebook would understand that
you had a relationship with them, and

00:08:19.732 --> 00:08:22.272
show you their photos and updates.

00:08:23.502 --> 00:08:27.632
As these products grew and
became more advanced, more

00:08:27.632 --> 00:08:29.634
complexity was added to this.

00:08:29.834 --> 00:08:34.114
You could follow pages of businesses,
you could express your interests,

00:08:34.384 --> 00:08:39.374
Facebook would see who you sent messages
to, it bought Instagram, and so on.

00:08:40.404 --> 00:08:45.074
Instagram, Twitter and Snapchat all
worked in slightly different ways,

00:08:45.094 --> 00:08:49.844
but the principle was the same:
you create an account, you create

00:08:49.864 --> 00:08:54.914
connections between people, and you
see the content that these people post.

00:08:56.024 --> 00:08:59.664
But the problem here is that
this isn’t always what people

00:08:59.674 --> 00:09:01.314
want to see and engage with.

00:09:01.994 --> 00:09:06.434
You might be Facebook friends with someone
you went to university with 15 years ago,

00:09:06.764 --> 00:09:12.554
or even school 60 years ago, but are you
interested in what they are doing now?

00:09:13.564 --> 00:09:18.044
You might have chosen to follow someone
on Instagram or Twitter because you’re

00:09:18.044 --> 00:09:22.664
interested in their tips about making
cookies, but do you want to hear

00:09:22.664 --> 00:09:24.444
their opinion about the World Cup?

00:09:25.244 --> 00:09:28.534
Sometimes, but often the answer is “no”.

00:09:29.624 --> 00:09:34.884
TikTok completely bypassed this,
it avoided the question of forming

00:09:34.984 --> 00:09:38.304
cross-directional relationships
between people altogether.

00:09:39.454 --> 00:09:43.974
Yes, you can follow people on TikTok,
in the same way as you can on other

00:09:43.974 --> 00:09:49.834
social networks, but TikTok’s focus is
on serving you videos that it thinks you

00:09:49.834 --> 00:09:52.404
will like, regardless of who made them.

00:09:53.234 --> 00:09:57.714
It’s the quality of the content
that matters, not your relationship

00:09:57.874 --> 00:09:59.394
with the person who created it.

00:10:00.614 --> 00:10:05.544
That’s why, when you open the TikTok
app, it opens on a page called “For

00:10:05.544 --> 00:10:10.344
you”, which could be any kind of video
that the app thinks you will enjoy.

00:10:11.594 --> 00:10:14.224
And how does it decide
what you will enjoy?

00:10:14.904 --> 00:10:16.684
Well, here’s the clever part.

00:10:17.604 --> 00:10:22.804
On a very superficial level, you can
say it’s “the algorithm”, the computer

00:10:22.824 --> 00:10:26.174
code that decides what you like
based on what you have liked before.

00:10:26.804 --> 00:10:31.254
But let’s go several levels deeper,
because it’s not just a case of there

00:10:31.264 --> 00:10:35.425
being an extremely smart set of computer
code sitting on a server somewhere.

00:10:36.505 --> 00:10:38.115
We need to talk about two things.

00:10:39.253 --> 00:10:43.269
First, the design of the
TikTok app, and how this is

00:10:43.269 --> 00:10:45.403
different to other social apps.

00:10:46.283 --> 00:10:52.087
Remember, you only ever see one video
per screen, so the TikTok algorithm can

00:10:52.087 --> 00:10:56.567
get a sense of your thoughts about that
video based on the actions you take.

00:10:57.437 --> 00:11:01.277
Do you swipe up right away
to move onto another video?

00:11:01.857 --> 00:11:04.657
OK, that indicates it wasn’t interesting.

00:11:05.407 --> 00:11:06.717
Did you watch it all?

00:11:07.257 --> 00:11:08.797
Good, that’s a promising start.

00:11:09.617 --> 00:11:12.687
Did you watch it all and
then tap the heart button?

00:11:13.267 --> 00:11:14.767
Better, you probably like it

00:11:15.237 --> 00:11:19.287
Did you watch it all several times,
tap the heart button, follow the

00:11:19.287 --> 00:11:23.387
person who made it, then send it to
lots of people and save the video?

00:11:23.947 --> 00:11:27.527
Boom, I think we’re in business,
you clearly like this a lot.

00:11:28.887 --> 00:11:34.017
When you contrast this to the information
that an app like Facebook or Twitter gets,

00:11:34.067 --> 00:11:38.987
where there are often multiple pieces
of content on the screen, Facebook and

00:11:38.987 --> 00:11:43.507
Twitter have more difficulty figuring out
what you actually think about something.

00:11:44.417 --> 00:11:49.037
If you scrolled past something,
did you just miss it, or were

00:11:49.037 --> 00:11:50.147
you not interested in it?

00:11:50.687 --> 00:11:54.437
If you stopped scrolling, which
piece of content were you looking at?

00:11:54.807 --> 00:11:58.837
Did you stop because you agreed or
disagreed with that piece of content?

00:11:59.977 --> 00:12:05.217
See, the entire design of TikTok makes
it far easier for the algorithm to

00:12:05.367 --> 00:12:07.577
figure out what you like and don’t like.

00:12:08.644 --> 00:12:13.480
And when it comes to the actual
content on TikTok, the videos that

00:12:13.480 --> 00:12:18.890
users make, the TikTok algorithm is
very good at recognising what is in a

00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:24.409
video, recognising people and objects
and general “stuff” that's going on.

00:12:25.525 --> 00:12:26.635
But that’s not all.

00:12:27.532 --> 00:12:32.072
This is combined with a team of people
who are going through the videos and

00:12:32.232 --> 00:12:37.722
manually checking and assigning tags
and categories to each video, so that

00:12:37.722 --> 00:12:43.353
when  the algorithm sees the actions
people take on these videos, all that

00:12:43.393 --> 00:12:49.023
information is stored and can be used to
make better recommendations in the future.

00:12:49.963 --> 00:12:53.804
Now to the second reason that this
TikTok recommendation algorithm

00:12:53.863 --> 00:12:56.033
is so good at recommending videos.

00:12:56.863 --> 00:13:01.593
Like every other social network,
TikTok’s algorithm relies heavily on

00:13:01.713 --> 00:13:06.323
machine learning, where an algorithm
is trained on large amounts of data.

00:13:07.113 --> 00:13:11.743
The more input data it has to
train on, the better the output,

00:13:11.883 --> 00:13:13.633
the better the recommendation.

00:13:14.703 --> 00:13:19.983
And this brings us back to the early
history of TikTok, and to Musical.ly,

00:13:20.153 --> 00:13:24.633
which was, you’ll remember, the
Chinese app that was very popular in

00:13:24.633 --> 00:13:26.343
the United States with teenage girls.

00:13:27.843 --> 00:13:32.923
When Musical.ly and Tiktok merged,
Tiktok got access to billions of

00:13:32.933 --> 00:13:37.333
hours of content that it could use
to train and improve its algorithm.

00:13:38.273 --> 00:13:40.673
This gave it a huge head start.

00:13:41.593 --> 00:13:46.783
And as more and more content is created
on TikTok the better its recommendation

00:13:46.807 --> 00:13:50.973
algorithm gets, the more time people
spend on it, the more videos are

00:13:50.973 --> 00:13:55.813
created, which in turn improves the
recommendation algorithm, and so on..

00:13:57.033 --> 00:14:01.153
Which brings us back to President
Trump at the start of the episode.

00:14:02.213 --> 00:14:09.613
By 2020, TikTok had more than 800 million
users outside of China, and was drawing

00:14:09.613 --> 00:14:11.783
the attention of American politicians.

00:14:12.803 --> 00:14:17.813
The advertising, reportedly more
than a billion dollars a year, was

00:14:17.813 --> 00:14:22.603
working, and the app was adding
millions of new users every single day.

00:14:23.553 --> 00:14:28.953
Now, why was this problematic, why did
it warrant President Trump proclaiming

00:14:28.953 --> 00:14:31.623
that he was looking at banning the app?

00:14:32.763 --> 00:14:34.273
Well, a few reasons.

00:14:35.113 --> 00:14:41.393
Firstly, TikTok’s parent company,
ByteDance, was Chinese, and–like

00:14:41.433 --> 00:14:46.063
any large Chinese company–had close
ties to the Chinese Communist Party.

00:14:47.105 --> 00:14:52.705
TikTok is technically an American
company, with data on its American

00:14:52.705 --> 00:14:58.938
users stored in the US, not in China,
but it was a perceived security threat.

00:14:59.878 --> 00:15:03.668
There was the worry of what TikTok
would do if it was asked by its

00:15:03.678 --> 00:15:08.038
parent company, and ultimately
asked by the Chinese government, to

00:15:08.038 --> 00:15:12.318
share personal data on its American
users with the Chinese government.

00:15:13.278 --> 00:15:17.652
As you’ve heard, the more you use
TikTok, the better it knows you, and

00:15:17.652 --> 00:15:22.662
so there were security concerns about
how this personal data could be used.

00:15:23.802 --> 00:15:28.472
Secondly, it was one thing to have a
company like Facebook, now of course

00:15:28.712 --> 00:15:32.802
“Meta”, but one thing to have an
American company like Facebook or

00:15:32.802 --> 00:15:38.132
Google be powerful and influential,
but to have hundreds of millions of

00:15:38.132 --> 00:15:44.022
Americans opening up a Chinese-made app
every day, in an era of increased trade

00:15:44.042 --> 00:15:47.062
protectionism, well that was a first.

00:15:48.202 --> 00:15:52.742
Thirdly, there were concerns about the
impact that TikTok was having on American

00:15:52.772 --> 00:15:55.172
culture, and society more widely.

00:15:56.362 --> 00:16:01.532
US TikTok users are now spending an
average of 80 minutes a day on the app,

00:16:01.942 --> 00:16:07.992
more than Facebook and Instagram combined,
primarily watching videos recommended

00:16:08.062 --> 00:16:10.422
by an algorithm developed in Beijing.

00:16:11.462 --> 00:16:13.352
Now, what’s wrong with this?

00:16:13.892 --> 00:16:18.882
Perhaps, nothing, it's simply a very
efficient algorithm and provides

00:16:18.892 --> 00:16:23.452
users with relevant and personalised
recommendations on the best content

00:16:23.462 --> 00:16:25.432
for them at any particular time.

00:16:26.812 --> 00:16:30.562
But sceptics have highlighted
the potential for this to be

00:16:30.562 --> 00:16:33.102
used in non-innocent ways.

00:16:34.132 --> 00:16:38.752
For example, if you wanted to reduce
the amount of educational content

00:16:38.892 --> 00:16:44.042
that was available to US teenagers and
increase the amount of socially divisive

00:16:44.082 --> 00:16:49.242
content, well, that can be done with a
tweak, a small change, of the algorithm.

00:16:50.699 --> 00:16:56.459
And the dangers of excessive social
media use by teenagers is well-known.

00:16:57.414 --> 00:17:02.444
In China, children under the
age of 14 are restricted from

00:17:02.444 --> 00:17:06.984
spending more than 40 minutes a
day on Douyin, the Chinese TikTok.

00:17:08.064 --> 00:17:13.654
Outside China, there is no such limit,
with many teenagers spending most

00:17:13.694 --> 00:17:16.074
of their day sucked into the app.

00:17:17.254 --> 00:17:23.514
So, the sceptics ask, why is this
app limited in China, but promoted so

00:17:23.514 --> 00:17:25.994
heavily and without any limits abroad?

00:17:26.994 --> 00:17:31.074
And it’s this that is perhaps
most alarming, this almost

00:17:31.084 --> 00:17:35.744
science-fiction like power of an
app to shape culture and society.

00:17:36.824 --> 00:17:41.874
Now, it should be said that TikTok
of course is not banned, and since

00:17:41.924 --> 00:17:46.184
Trump spoke about potentially banning
it, it has gone from strength to

00:17:46.184 --> 00:17:50.324
strength, not just in the United
States but all over the world.

00:17:51.044 --> 00:17:56.444
There are almost a billion international
TikTok users, and the app has experienced

00:17:56.454 --> 00:18:01.044
huge success in places with very
little cultural similarities to China.

00:18:01.714 --> 00:18:05.384
In the Middle East, for example,
TikTok is hugely popular.

00:18:05.754 --> 00:18:10.774
It’s popular in Indonesia, Brazil,
France, Iceland, all over the world.

00:18:11.634 --> 00:18:15.904
And this is the beauty, you could
say, of the way in which the

00:18:15.914 --> 00:18:17.654
recommendation algorithm works.

00:18:17.964 --> 00:18:22.724
It surpasses, it jumps over
cultural norms and traditions.

00:18:23.474 --> 00:18:28.204
All that matters is what
you, as a TikTok user, like.

00:18:29.244 --> 00:18:34.564
If you use TikTok, you’ll probably know
all too well that the algorithm has an

00:18:34.564 --> 00:18:39.324
incredible way of showing you videos
that you like, no matter your interests.

00:18:40.434 --> 00:18:46.834
If you like fish, “fishtok” has 17
billion views, medieval role playing

00:18:46.834 --> 00:18:51.874
videos have 4 billion views, and you
may well have seen that there is no

00:18:51.874 --> 00:18:57.184
shortage of English teachers dancing
around and teaching you idioms or telling

00:18:57.184 --> 00:18:59.504
you you need to stop saying “I’m fine”.

00:19:00.294 --> 00:19:04.404
By the way, I think it’s absolutely
fine to say “I’m fine”, but of course

00:19:04.504 --> 00:19:08.004
it’s the controversial viewpoints
that get all the attention on TikTok.

00:19:09.164 --> 00:19:14.624
Now, another interesting development,
or implication of the way the TikTok

00:19:14.624 --> 00:19:18.714
recommendation algorithm works, is
that it has made it far easier for

00:19:18.714 --> 00:19:23.884
people to find videos even made by
small, relatively unknown people.

00:19:25.074 --> 00:19:30.324
If you compare this to YouTube or
Instagram, for example, previously

00:19:30.324 --> 00:19:34.974
with these apps you would only see
content from people you follow, which

00:19:35.094 --> 00:19:39.504
in many cases would be celebrities
or people with large followings.

00:19:40.544 --> 00:19:46.854
With TikTok, because the algorithm is not
primarily based on friends or followers,

00:19:46.854 --> 00:19:52.646
videos can go viral based on merit alone,
based on how entertaining they are,

00:19:53.014 --> 00:19:55.594
which has led to a burst of creativity.

00:19:56.364 --> 00:20:02.374
The TikTok app makes it very easy for
anyone to create funny videos using only

00:20:02.374 --> 00:20:07.354
their phone, so now anyone in the world
has the chance of creating something

00:20:07.474 --> 00:20:11.774
that will be seen by millions of people,
you don’t have to be Kim Kardashian.

00:20:13.084 --> 00:20:17.984
And, of course, the easier it is to
create videos and be seen by millions of

00:20:17.994 --> 00:20:22.324
people, the more people create videos,
and the more people create videos, the

00:20:22.504 --> 00:20:27.174
more input data the algorithm has, the
better it gets, the more people come back

00:20:27.194 --> 00:20:32.444
to TikTok, the more people create videos,
as you can see it is a virtuous circle.

00:20:33.404 --> 00:20:36.437
And all this leads us
back to the present day.

00:20:37.357 --> 00:20:43.464
While Facebook, Snapchat and YouTube were
all too happy to take TikTok’s billions of

00:20:43.474 --> 00:20:48.734
marketing dollars, they have now realised
that TikTok has been eating their lunch.

00:20:49.884 --> 00:20:54.404
Every minute spent on TikTok is a
minute that can’t be spent on another

00:20:54.404 --> 00:21:00.068
social network, and in a business
where eyeballs and time equal money,

00:21:00.531 --> 00:21:06.032
TikTok has gone from a  customer to a
competitor, perhaps even, a predator.

00:21:07.336 --> 00:21:13.246
And what this has led to is an increasing
TikTok-ization of apps like Facebook

00:21:13.246 --> 00:21:18.736
and Instagram, where your friends and
followers are being deprioritised in

00:21:18.736 --> 00:21:21.296
favour of algorithmic recommendations.

00:21:22.176 --> 00:21:26.976
If you’re a user of these apps, you’ll
probably have seen this already, with

00:21:27.266 --> 00:21:31.920
“for you” style tabs where you are shown
content that the app thinks you will like.

00:21:33.060 --> 00:21:37.280
And, according to most
commentators, this is bound to

00:21:37.280 --> 00:21:40.570
continue because…well, it works.

00:21:41.470 --> 00:21:46.160
Until TikTok, there was very little
true innovation in social media

00:21:46.160 --> 00:21:50.680
apps, the innovation there was was
usually swiftly copied by others.

00:21:51.350 --> 00:21:55.670
“Stories” was first a Snapchat
development, before it was copied

00:21:55.670 --> 00:21:57.660
by Instagram and then Facebook.

00:21:58.470 --> 00:22:02.620
Twitter “Spaces” is the same
idea as “Clubhouse”, and there

00:22:02.620 --> 00:22:04.090
are countless other examples.

00:22:05.110 --> 00:22:10.780
The innovation of TikTok was to completely
flip the “social” element of social

00:22:10.780 --> 00:22:16.780
media on its head, and instead approach
the problem more as “how can we show you

00:22:16.780 --> 00:22:19.450
the most entertaining video right now?”

00:22:20.760 --> 00:22:25.177
As it turns out, it doesn’t matter
who made the video, they could be

00:22:25.177 --> 00:22:28.457
your best friend or they could be
someone on the other side of the

00:22:28.457 --> 00:22:30.067
world that you’ve never seen before.

00:22:31.157 --> 00:22:36.527
And this is the real power, you could
say the “equalising” power, of TikTok.

00:22:37.497 --> 00:22:43.497
So, to conclude this exploration into
this hugely influential app, even if

00:22:43.497 --> 00:22:48.877
you never download or install TikTok,
you will experience the effects of

00:22:48.927 --> 00:22:54.727
TikTok on culture, society, and on the
products and services you use, you’ll

00:22:54.737 --> 00:22:59.377
see how TikTok has already changed the
world, and will continue to change it.

00:23:00.627 --> 00:23:05.957
If you look on the TikTok website,
you’ll find the words “ Our mission is

00:23:05.987 --> 00:23:09.057
